The Saginaw Bay Regional Friendly Society

The purpose of the Saginaw Bay Regional Friendly Society is to facilitate the mutual welfare of its members, while itself remaining apart from all authoritarian and irrational influences.

“[A friendly society] is a mutual organization or benefit society composed of a body of people who join together for a common financial or social purpose. Before modern insurance, and the welfare state, friendly societies provided financial and social services to individuals, often according to their religious, political, or trade affiliations.”

— Wikipedia
